- content_for :page_header_text do
  %h3= 'Platform Layout'

- content_for :page_header do
  = render 'shared/page_header'

- content_for :page_body do
  %p The platform layout refers to the base html structure required to include and use the platform assets and the design of the header, navigation, and page title used for platform apps. Applications using sandman will automatically have access to all the stylesheets and javascript/jquery functionality provided, but must follow certain rules to achieve the best results. The applications also do not need to be checkmated to have the header available to them. Sandman includes a header partial(for Rails apps) that mimics the checkmate header and has an API built in to help create the dropdowns and links in the header and navigation. The page header (blue area below the navigation) must be included by the application and has documented areas that wil be affected by the platform styles.

  .panel.panel-default
    .panel-heading
      %h3.panel-title Base HTML Structure
    .panel-body
      %p The minimum HTML structure required to include the platform assets
      %code
        %pre
          :escaped
            <!DOCTYPE html>
            <!--[if IE 8]><html class="no-js lt-ie9"> <![endif]-->
            <!--[if gt IE 8]><!--> <html class="no-js"> <!--<![endif]-->
            <head>

                <meta charset="utf-8">
                <meta http-equiv="X-UA-Compatible" content="IE=edge,chrome=1">
                <title>Medidata Clinical Cloud</title>

                <meta name="description" content="">
                <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1">

                <title>Document</title>

                <!-- Modernizr -->
                <script src="modernizr.js"></script>

                <!-- Stylesheets -->
                <link rel="stylesheet" href="platform.css">

                <link rel="stylesheet" href="application.css">

                <!-- AVOID OTHER JAVASCRIPT IN THE HEADER -->

            </head>
            <body>
              <!-- Application/Platform layout -->

              <!-- Scripts at the bottom -->
              <script src="jquery.js"></script>
              <script src="platform.js"></script>
              <script src="application.js"></script>
            </body>
      %div
        - md_file = File.read("#{Rails.root}/app/views/sandman/markdown/platform_layout_base.md")
        = md_file.markdown_to_html
  .panel.panel-default
    .panel-heading
      %h3.panel-title Platform Header and Navigation
    .panel-body
      %p The HTML structure with CSS classes properly applied to produce the common header, navigation, and page header.
      %code
        %pre
          :escaped
            <!-- header -->
            <header id="header">
              <!-- header content -->
            </header>

            <!-- navigation -->
            <nav id="navigation">
              <!-- navigation content -->
            </nav>

            <!--  master application content -->
            <div id="main">

              <!-- APPLICTION UI CODE GOES HERE -->

            </div>

            <!-- footer -->
            <footer id="footer">Content TBD</footer>
      .dom-diagram
        = image_tag('/assets/sandman/header_structure.png')
      %div
        - md_file = File.read("#{Rails.root}/app/views/sandman/markdown/platform_layout_header.md")
        = md_file.markdown_to_html

  .panel.panel-default
    .panel-heading
      %h3.panel-title Page Header
    .panel-body
      %p The HTML structure of the Page Header (blue area below the navigation)
      %code
        %pre
          :escaped
            <!-- app content wraper -->
            <div id="main">
              <!-- page header main -->
              <div class="page-header page-header-main clearfix">
                <div class="container-fluid">
                  <div class="page-header-text">
                    <h2>Page Header Text</h2>
                  </div>
                  <div class="page-header-controls">
                    <a href="" class="btn btn-default"><span class="fa fa-glass"></span> Button</a>
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>

              <!-- Add your site or application content here -->
              <!-- wrap keeps the site anchored on the left -->
                <div class="container-fluid"> Application Content </div>
            </div>
      .dom-diagram
        = image_tag('/assets/sandman/platform-layout-dom.png')
      %div
        - md_file = File.read("#{Rails.root}/app/views/sandman/markdown/platform_layout_pageheader.md")
        = md_file.markdown_to_html

